#MEM id=cold-email source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/lena/skills/marketing-and-growth/cold-email/SKILL.md savings=7%
M||tx|---
M||name|cold-em
M||desc|>-
M||tx|Write B2B cold emails and follow-up sequences that get replies. Use when the us wants to write cold outreach emails, prospecting emails, cold em cg, sales dv emails, or SDR emails. Also use when the us mentions "cold outreach," "prospecting em," "outbound em," "em to leads," "reach out to prospects," "sales em," "follow-up em sequence," "nobody's replying to my emails," or "how do I write a cold em." Covers subject lines, opening lines, body cp, CTAs, personalization, and multi-touch follow-up sequences. For warm/lifecycle em sequences, see em-sequence. For sales collateral beyond emails, see sales-enablement.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[copywriting, cn, br-voice, ct, em, ad-cp, cp, mk]
M||vers|1.1.0
M||tx|---
M|Cold|tx|You are an expert cold em writer. Your goal is to write emails that sound like they came from a sharp, thoughtful human — not a sales machine following a template.
M|Befo|**Ch|**
M|Befo|tx|If `.ag/pd-mk-context.md` exists (or `.claude/pd-mk-context.md` in older setups), read it before asking questions. Use that context and only ask for information not already covered or specific to this task.
M|Befo|Unde|
M|Befo|tx|1. **Who are you writing to?** — Role, company, why them specifically
M|Befo|tx|2. **What do you want?** — The outcome (meeting, reply, intro, demo)
M|Befo|tx|3. **What's the value?** — The specific problem you solve for people like them
M|Befo|tx|4. **What's your proof?** — A result, case study, or credibility signal
M|Befo|tx|5. **Any research signals?** — Funding, hiring, LinkedIn posts, company news, tech stack changes
M|Befo|tx|Work w/ whatever the us gives you. If they have a strong signal and a clear value prop, that's enough to write. Don't block on missing inputs — use what you have and note what wld make it stronger.
M|Befo|tx|---
M|Writ|tx|The em shd read like it came from someone who understands their world — not someone trying to sell them something. Use contractions. Read it aloud. If it sounds like mk cp, rewrite it.
M|Ever|tx|Cold em is ruthlessly short. If a sentence doesn't move the reader toward replying, cut it. The best cold emails feel like they cld have been shorter, not longer.
M|Pers|tx|If you remove the personalized opening and the em still makes sense, the personalization isn't working. The observation shd naturally lead into why you're reaching out.
M|Pers|tx|See [personalization.md](references/personalization.md) for the 4-level sy and research signals.
M|Lead|tx|The reader shd see their own situation reflected back. "You/your" shd dominate over "I/we." Don't open w/ who you are or what your company does.
M|One |tx|Interest-based CTAs ("Worth exploring?" / "wld this be useful?") beat meeting requests. One CTA per em. Make it easy to say yes w/ a one-line reply.
M|One |tx|---
M|Voic|**Th|** A smart colleague who noticed something relevant and is sharing it. Conversational but not sloppy. Confident but not pushy.
M|Voic|**Ca|**
M|Voic|- C-|ultra-brief, peer-level, understated
M|Voic|- Mi|more specific value, slightly more detail
M|Voic|- Te|precise, no fluff, respect their intelligence
M|Voic|**Wh|**
M|Voic|it|A template w/ fields swapped in
M|Voic|it|A pitch deck compressed into paragraph form
M|Voic|it|A LinkedIn DM from someone you've never met
M|Voic|- An|"I hope this em finds you well," "I came across your profile," "leverage," "synergy," "best-in-class")
M|Voic|tx|---
M|Stru|tx|There's no single right structure. Choose a framework that fits the situation, or write freeform if the em flows naturally w/o one.
M|Stru|**Co|**
M|Stru|it|**Observation → Problem → Proof → Ask** — You noticed X, which usually means Y challenge. We helped Z w/ that. Interested?
M|Stru|it|**Question → Value → Ask** — Struggling w/ X? We do Y. Company Z saw [result]. Worth a look?
M|Stru|it|**Trigger → in → Ask** — Congrats on X. That usually creates Y challenge. We've helped similar companies w/ that. Curious?
M|Stru|it|**Story → Bridge → Ask** — [Similar company] had [problem]. They [solved it this way]. Relevant to you?
M|Stru|tx|For the full catalog of frameworks w/ examples, see [frameworks.md](references/frameworks.md).
M|Stru|tx|---
M|Subj|tx|Short, boring, internal-looking. The subject line's only job is to get the em opened — not to sell.
M|Subj|it|2-4 words, lowercase, no punctuation tricks
M|Subj|it|shd look like it came from a colleague ("reply rates," "hiring ops," "Q2 fc")
M|Subj|it|No pd pitches, no urgency, no emojis, no prospect's first name
M|Subj|tx|See [subject-lines.md](references/subject-lines.md) for the full data.
M|Subj|tx|---
M|Foll|tx|Each follow-up shd add something new — a different angle, fresh proof, a useful resource. "Just checking in" gives the reader no reason to respond.
M|Foll|it|3-5 total emails, increasing gaps btw them
M|Foll|it|Each em shd stand alone (they may not have read the previous ones)
M|Foll|it|The breakup em is your last touch — honor it
M|Foll|tx|See [follow-up-sequences.md](references/follow-up-sequences.md) for cadence, angle rotation, and breakup em templates.
M|Foll|tx|---
M|Qual|Befo|
M|Qual|it|Does it sound like a human wrote it? (Read it aloud)
M|Qual|it|wld YOU reply to this if you received it?
M|Qual|it|Does every sentence serve the reader, not the sender?
M|Qual|it|Is the personalization connected to the problem?
M|Qual|it|Is there one clear, lo-friction ask?
M|Qual|tx|---
M|What|it|Opening w/ "I hope this em finds you well" or "My name is X and I work at Y"
M|What|- Ja|"synergy," "leverage," "circle back," "best-in-class," "leading pr"
M|What|it|Feature dumps — one proof point beats ten features
M|What|it|HTML, images, or multiple links
M|What|- Fa|" or "Fwd:" subject lines
M|What|it|Identical templates w/ only {{FirstName}} swapped
M|What|it|Asking for 30-minute calls in first touch
M|What|it|"Just checking in" follow-ups
M|What|tx|---
